                                    <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                                </svg>
                                <span>15:22</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="sm:pl-6">
                    <p class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl leading-none font-extrabold text-gray-900 tracking-tight mb-8">An API for your design&nbsp;system.</p>
                    <p class="max-w-4xl text-lg sm:text-2xl font-medium sm:leading-10 space-y-6 mb-6">
                        Utility classes help you work within the constraints of a system instead of littering your stylesheets with arbitrary values. They make it easy to be consistent with color choices, spacing, typography, shadows, and
